The article discusses how the COVID-19 pandemic has exacerbated the challenges faced by small businesses in the US, such as aging infrastructure, workforce constraints, and a tax code that favors large corporations. It highlights the importance of infrastructure investments, broadband projects, and improving local roads and bridges for the success of small businesses. The American Jobs Plan is introduced as a solution to address these issues by upgrading transportation infrastructure, providing universal broadband, and training American workers for future jobs. The plan also includes direct support to small businesses, such as increased access to federal contracts and investments in financing and technical assistance programs. Additionally, President Biden's Made in America Tax Plan aims to level the playing field between small businesses and large corporations by rewarding investment at home and changing how corporations are taxed worldwide.